"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-paris-olympics-2024-team-south-africa-in-action-on-sunday-28-july-results-schedule-breaking\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024: Team SA in action on Sunday, 28 July  Team SA head into Day 3 of the Paris Olympics 2024 with one medal in the bank, courtesy of the men's rugby sevens team.  Team SAhead into the third day of theParis Olympics 2024with one medal in the bank, courtesy of the men's rugby sevens team who took the bronze medal.  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  There is a full day of competition, with Team SA involved in10sports, but only one (mountain bike cycling) is a medals event.  Follow all the latest updates clickHERE.  All times SA.  Women's MTB cross-country (14:10):Candice Lill  Eventing, cross-country (10:30-15:00):Alexander Peternell  Men's epee, table of 64 (10:00):Harry Sanee vs Vadim Sharlaimov (Kaz)  Men's epee, table of 32 (12:25):Harry Sanee TBC  Men's epee, table of 16 (15:05):Harry Sanee TBC  Men's epee, table of 8 (16:25):Harry Sanee TBC  Men's epee, semi-finals (20:00):Harry Sanee TBC  Women's artistic, qualifying (09:30):Caitlin Rooskrantz  Women's Pool B (12:45):Team SA vs Australia  Men's Pool A (20:15):Team SA vs Great Britain  Men's pair, heats (11:20):Christopher Baxter and John Smith  Women's Pool B (16:00):Team SA vs Australia  Women's Pool B (19:00):Team SA vs Ireland  Women's 100m breaststroke, heats (11:36):Tatjana Smith  Men's 100m backstroke, heats (11:54):Pieter Coetze  Women's 200m freestyle, heats (12:12):Aimee Canny  Women's 100m butterfly, final (20:40):Erin Gallagher TBC  Women's 100m breaststroke, semi-finals (21:10):Tatjana Smith TBC  Men's 100m backstroke, semi-finals (21:32):Pieter Coetze TBC  Women's 200m freestyle, semi-finals (21:50):Aimee Canny TBC  Women's street prelims (12:00):Boipelo Awuah  Women's street final (17:00):Boipelo Awuah TBC  Women's second round (19:00):Sarah Baum vs Camila Kemp (Ger)  Men's round 2 (11:48):Jordy Smith and Matt McGillivray  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"